<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<!--
  Opaque baseline. PartDesign::Revolution is not typed yet in the
  reader (FreeCadReader.cpp's feature dispatch has no Revolution
  branch), so it falls through to the catch-all FeatPayloadOpaque
  with strings["freecad_type"]="PartDesign::Revolution" and
  FeatType::Unknown.

  This is intentional. The IR golden's `payload=opaque
  freecad_type=PartDesign::Revolution` line is the coverage
  thermometer the README talks about: the day someone wires
  Revolution into the dispatch, this line flips from `opaque ...`
  to `revolve sketch_id=2 axis_o=... axis_d=... angle=...`, and
  the diff between the old and new golden IS the proof of new
  coverage.

  The sketch is a single line off-axis -- a degenerate profile
  but enough to satisfy the dispatcher; the Revolution payload
  doesn't get parsed yet so its Angle / ReferenceAxis attributes
  are ignored. Once Revolution becomes typed, swap the file for
  a meaningful profile + axis ref and re-mint.
-->
